latestPosts.caption: Start today and it’ll be the best decision of your life ♥️🤌🏾🎀

One of the questions we get asked most often is:
“What all can I do in 3–4 months?”

And honestly, our answer will always be:
“What all you can do in 3–4 months.”

Because when it comes to art, growth isn’t one-size-fits-all. Everyone’s journey is different—and that’s the beauty of it.

But what we can tell you is this:
Our syllabus, techniques, and teaching methods are tried, tested, and trusted by hundreds of students. They’re designed to set you up for real, lasting progress.

So if you’re curious, here’s what we know is possible in just 4 months—with consistency, patience, and a little bit of fire in your belly.🔥

Often times we conduct surprise showcases like this one here, just to give them a reality check about

1. Grace while moving 
2. Lightness in movement
3. If they can do it on both sides 
4. Emphasis on correlation to movement and feeling good 

This is what May looked like for this batch ❤️

Most dreams come true ♥️🎀🤗

Watching a student turn into a teacher is the most satisfying feeling I’ve ever experienced.

"Wherever you go, that's where I'll follow
Nobody's promised tomorrow
So I'ma love you every night like it's the last night"
@thepolecamp is my Home. ❤️ ✨Period.✨
What this community and experience has given me is irreplaceable. 

This routine is imperfect, but it's mine 💜💪🏽💅🏽
✨ Until we pole again!!! 🫶🏽✨

@sofiapremkumar I didn't know I could flow like this, thank you for this amazing choreo and for gracing us with your skill and vibes. 🤌🏽 

#poledance #polesport #polefit #flow #dancereels

The whole @thepolecamp journey has nothing but made me stronger mentally, emotionally and physically. Wouldn’t call them trainers but power rangers @_ms.raju_ , @vasundhra.verma7 , @prarthanasrinivasaraja , @monika.selvan_ , each one of them made sure they bring out the best in us and filled us with so much of good energy. It’s like I have unlocked a new door in my life. Can’t thank you enough @anushaswamy for the camp 🤍 this truly was a special experience. Oh and the song 💖  #poledance #bangalore #thebrowneyedgirl #anaghakrishnan #polecamp #poledanceindia #whatifyoufly

Somethin’ so out of the ordinary because I Unlocked a personal record -  1.32 mins ON and around pole. A wonderful choreo and some tricks learnt through the month of May.  Thank You @thepolecamp, @anushaswamy @vasundhra.verma7 @monika.selvan_ and @_ms.raju_  for the guidance and constant motivation.

✨ Weekend of Pole: 3 Styles, Trial Classes ✨
One weekend. Three unique styles. All the ways your body can move, feel, and express.

🌪️ Spin Pole – Glide and flow with momentum. This style teaches you how to harness spin and create graceful, continuous movement.

🌟 Pole Sport – Focus on strength, technique, and control. Learn how to hold shapes and move with intention on a still pole.

👠 Pole Muse – Explore sensuality, musicality, and choreography in heels. Build confidence through movement that feels as good as it looks.

All levels are welcome 🤌🏾
DM to register
